#: ../../library/urllib.request.rst:222
msgid ""
"This helper function returns a dictionary of scheme to proxy server URL "
"mappings. It scans the environment for variables named ``<scheme>_proxy``, "
"in a case insensitive approach, for all operating systems first, and when it "
"cannot find it, looks for proxy information from System Configuration for "
"macOS and Windows Systems Registry for Windows. If both lowercase and "
"uppercase environment variables exist (and disagree), lowercase is preferred."
msgstr ""
"Denna hjﾃ､lpfunktion returnerar en ordbok med URL-mappningar mellan schema "
"och proxyserver. Den sﾃｶker i miljﾃｶn efter variabler med namnet "
"``<scheme>_proxy``, utan hﾃ､nsyn till versaler, fﾃｶr alla operativsystem "
"fﾃｶrst, och nﾃ､r den inte hittar den sﾃｶker den efter proxyinformation frﾃ･n "
"System Configuration fﾃｶr macOS och Windows Systems Registry fﾃｶr Windows. Om "
"det finns miljﾃｶvariabler med bﾃ･de smﾃ･ och stora bokstﾃ､ver (och de inte ﾃ､r "
"ﾃｶverens) fﾃｶredras smﾃ･ bokstﾃ､ver."

#: ../../library/urllib.request.rst:232
msgid ""
"If the environment variable ``REQUEST_METHOD`` is set, which usually "
"indicates your script is running in a CGI environment, the environment "
"variable ``HTTP_PROXY`` (uppercase ``_PROXY``) will be ignored. This is "
